<h3><a href="/vnews/display.v/ART/5e8dfcebbd22b">Avery FFA or Junior FFA </a></h3>
<div class="socs-feature-text">
<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt"><span style="font-size:20px;"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="line-height:107%">Dear Parents,</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt"> </p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt"><span style="font-size:20px;"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="line-height:107%">As you already know Avery ISD is extending the school closure through May 1<sup>st </sup>as a result of the continued restrictions and concerns regarding the coronavirus. The uncertainty surrounding this virus is the hardest thing to handle. We don’t know how exactly we’ll be impacted going forward. The uncomfortable answer is we don’t know. With that said, we have a little over seven weeks left in this school year and it’s time to start planning the next one.  The one item that is pressing over the next few weeks is county fair projects for this coming September. There are many different livestock projects students can participate in such as Market Lambs, Goats, Swine, Rabbits and Commercial or Registered Heifers. If you are interested in showing a project under the Avery FFA or Junior FFA program, let me know. Remember you can start showing at county if you are entering Kindergarten. If you plan on purchasing an animal on your own, please notify me. The Ag. Department needs to keep a head count of all animals on feed to plan out our summer. If you need help finding livestock, get a hold of me soon. This will allow us a chance to find everyone a quality project. More than ever a good line of communication with each other is important. You can call the Ag Building at 903-684-3436 (leave voice mail) or email me at </span><a href="mailto:keith.westbrook@averyisd.net" style="color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline"><span style="line-height:107%">keith.westbrook@averyisd.net</span></a><span style="line-height:107%"> for check in dates, rules and procedures. </span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt"><span style="font-size:20px;"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="line-height:107%">I know this is a difficult time for everyone and we appreciate your patience as we work toward a solution. I am here to help as we all work together to support each other during these unprecedented times.</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt"> </p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt"><span style="font-size:20px;"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="line-height:107%">Sincerely,</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt"> </p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt"><span style="font-size:20px;"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="line-height:107%">Keith Westbrook</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt"><span style="font-size:20px;"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="line-height:107%">Agri-Science Instructor/FFA Advisor</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt"> </p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt"> </p>
